# Cloudflare Pages routing for the WeHA single-page app.
#
# - /api/* is served by Pages Functions (see _routes.json) and is never
#   rewritten here, so API calls always reach the functions.
# - Every client route is prerendered to its own static HTML by react-snap, so
#   deep links and refreshes (e.g. /services) resolve directly to real files.
# - Any unmatched path is served the app shell via build/404.html (generated in
#   the postbuild step), which boots React Router client-side.
#
# We intentionally do NOT add a "/*  /index.html  200" catch-all: Cloudflare
# rejects it as an "infinite loop" (the /index.html destination is itself
# matched by /*), so the rule is ignored and breaks deep links. The 404.html
# fallback above achieves the same SPA behaviour without the loop.
